title: Schedule breakdown: A quick look at Utah's football scheduled
text:
Published: Monday, Oct. 12 2015 9:25 a.m. MDT Updated: 9 minutes ago Utah MUSS as the University of Utah defeats Cal 30-24 in PAC12 NCAA football Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015,in Salt Lake City Utah. Tom Smart, 
Utes defeat California 30-24 at Rice-Eccles Stadium Saturday and improve to 5-0 overall and 2-0 in Pac-12 play. 
MICHIGAN (5-1): Defeated Northwestern, 38-0. Up next: Saturday vs. Michigan State (6-0). 
UTAH STATE (3-2): Defeated Fresno State, 56-14. Up next: Friday vs. Boise State (5-1). 
FRESNO STATE (1-5): Lost to Utah State, 56-14. Up next: Friday vs. UNLV (2-4). 
OREGON (3-3, 1-2): Lost to Washington State, 45-38 (2OT). Up next: Saturday at Washington (3-2, 1-1). 
CALIFORNIA (5-1, 2-1): Lost at Utah, 30-24. Up next: Oct. 22 at UCLA (4-1, 1-1). 
ARIZONA STATE (4-2, 2-1): Defeated Colorado, 48-23. Up next: Saturday at Utah (5-0, 2-0). 
USC (3-2, 1-2): Lost to Washington, 17-12. Up next: Saturday at Notre Dame (5-1). 
OREGON STATE (2-3, 0-2): Lost at Arizona, 44-7. Up next: Saturday at Washington State (3-2, 1-1). 
WASHINGTON (3-2, 1-1): Defeated USC, 17-12. Up next: Saturday vs. Oregon (3-3, 1-2). 
ARIZONA (4-2, 1-2): Defeated Oregon State, 44-7. Up next: Saturday at Colorado (3-3, 0-2). 
UCLA (4-1, 1-1): Had a bye. Up next: Thursday at Stanford (4-1, 3-0). 
COLORADO (3-3, 0-2): Lost at Arizona State, 48-23. Up next: Saturday vs. Arizona (4-2, 1-2). Recommended Stories
